#week-title("Three", "The Inner Fire & Its Circulation")

=== Core Teaching

The alchemical tradition speaks of a *Secret Fire* that is present in all living
things — distinct from both the physical warmth of metabolism and the abstract
concept of soul. This is the vital fire itself: the concentrated expression of
the World Spirit within the individual organism. The practitioner who has
developed the inner flame practice from Year One Month 3 has already begun to
work with this directly.

In Paracelsian understanding, the inner fire circulates through the subtle body
via channels that correspond to the Middle Pillar of the Tree of Life. It can
be made conscious through directed breath and attentive awareness. This is not
a metaphor for physiological processes (though those processes exist in parallel)
— it is a directly perceivable phenomenon that becomes available to developed
inner attention.

*The Threefold Breath revisited at depth.* The Threefold Breath introduced in
Year One Month 2 — Mercury channel (right/white), Sulphur channel (left/red),
Salt channel (centre/blue) — is now practised with greater subtlety. At the
Year One level, the practice trains the perception of the three principles as
distinct channels. At the Year Two level, the relationship between the channels
becomes the focus: how does the Mercury inform the Sulphur? How does the Salt
ground and fix what the other two channels circulate?

*Somatic awareness as alchemical practice.* The practitioner who has developed
genuine somatic sensitivity — who has learned to distinguish between mere
physical sensation and the subtler felt-sense of the vital force — brings an
instrument to the laboratory that no external technology can provide: the direct
perception of whether a preparation is alive or dead, whether the vital force
is present or has been destroyed. This sensitivity is built slowly through the
body-awareness practice introduced this month.

*The body-awareness practice.* Ten minutes per day, ideally after the
meditation and before the laboratory session. Sit comfortably. Begin at the
crown of the head and allow awareness to descend, region by region, through the
face, throat, chest, arms, belly, pelvis, legs, and feet. At each region, simply
notice: warmth or coolness, tension or ease, aliveness or numbness. Do not
try to change anything. Simply attend.

=== Topics This Week

- The Secret Fire as a directly perceivable phenomenon
- Revisiting the Threefold Breath at depth: the relationship between channels
- Somatic awareness as a perceptual instrument for laboratory work
- The body-awareness practice: method and purpose

#inner-work[
  *The Secret Fire Practice*

  After your morning meditation, spend ten minutes with the body-awareness
  practice (crown to feet, noticing without changing).

  Then remain seated for five minutes more and return to the inner flame from
  Year One. Now, rather than simply holding the image of the flame, allow it
  to become part of the somatic scan: is the inner fire present throughout the
  body, or concentrated in certain regions? Does it feel different in the centre
  than in the periphery?

  Record two things: (1) what you observed in the body-awareness scan, and (2)
  the quality and distribution of the inner fire as you perceived it.
]

